.SH NAME
Document.visibilityState \- Document: visibilityState property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Document.visibilityState\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property
returns the visibility of the document.
It can be used to check whether the document is in the background or in
a minimized window, or is otherwise not visible to the user.
.PP
When the value of this property changes, the \f[CR]visibilitychange\f[R]
event is sent to the \f[CR]Document\f[R].
.PP
The \f[CR]Document.hidden\f[R] property provides an alternative way to
determine whether the page is hidden.
.SH VALUE
A string with one of the following values:
.TP
\f[B]visible\f[R]
The page content may be at least partially visible.
In practice this means that the page is the foreground tab of a
non\-minimized window.
.TP
\f[B]hidden\f[R]
The page content is not visible to the user.
In practice this means that the document is either a background tab or
part of a minimized window, or the OS screen lock is active.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
document.addEventListener(\(dqvisibilitychange\(dq, () \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(document.visibilityState);
  \f[I]// Modify behavior\&...\f[R]
});
.EE
